3.00	Sneak_Attack_(album)	Sneak Attack (album)	Sneak Attack is the name of an album released by the Buddy Miles Regiment in 1981. This band was headed by American rock guitarist and drummer, Buddy Miles. The album was released as an 11-track 2-LP vinyl set, and included tracks that were recorded live at the CIM prison facility in Chino, California.This Album was co-produced by Jim Paris and recorded and mastered at 3 different recording studios in Los Angeles, California, including the live show at Chino State Prison where Buddy formed an all inmate band while serving time there.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/3/38/Sneak-Attack.jpg/220px-Sneak-Attack.jpg
